Gemini: [SECTION_TAG] 1. CHECK GIT REPOSITORY ROOT:

Action: Open a terminal/command prompt and navigate to the root of your ai-execution-system folder (the folder containing app.py, cloudbuild.yaml, etc., not the terraform subfolder).
Action: Run command: git status
Expected Result: git status should show you are in a Git repository. If it says "Not a git repository", you are in the wrong folder.
Troubleshooting: Make sure you are in the ai-execution-system root folder, not ai-execution-system\deployment\terraform. The git push needs to be executed from the repository root.
[SECTION_TAG] 2. CHECK CURRENT BRANCH & REMOTE TRACKING:

Action: Run command: git branch -v
Expected Result: This shows your local branches. You should see * main (or similar indicating you are on the main branch). It should also show if main is tracking a remote branch. It might look like: * main [origin/main] Your last commit message... The [origin/main] part indicates it's tracking the remote main branch.
Troubleshooting (If not tracking):
If you are on main but it's not tracking origin/main, try: git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/main main
Then try git push origin main again.
[SECTION_TAG] 3. CHECK FOR LOCAL COMMITS:

Action: Run command: git log
Expected Result: git log should show your recent commits, including the "Test Cloud Build Trigger - Updated print in app.py" commit. If it shows "fatal: your current branch 'main' does not have any commits yet", there are no commits to push on the current branch.
Troubleshooting (No commits): If no commits, ensure you did git add app.py and git commit -m "..." before trying to push. If you did commit, double-check you are on the correct branch (git branch).
[SECTION_TAG] 4. VERIFY REMOTE URL (Less Likely, but check):

Action: Run command: git remote -v
Expected Result: This lists your configured remotes. You should see origin pointing to your GitHub repository URL ( https://github.com/palios-taey/ai-execution-system.git).
Troubleshooting (Incorrect URL): If the URL is wrong, you can update it: git remote set-url origin <your_correct_github_repo_url>
[CONCISE_ACTIONS_TAG] Concise Actions - Push Fix:

cd C:\ai-execution-system (Go to repo root)
git status (Verify in Git repo)
git branch -v (Check branch & tracking)
git log (Check for commits)
If needed: git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/main main
git push origin main (Try push again from repo root)
Let me know:

Are you running git push from C:\ai-execution-system?
What does git status, git branch -v, and git log show?
After trying these checks, does git push origin main work from the ai-execution-system root folder?
